article.headline: Morgan St. 71, Norfolk St. 61
article.story: BALTIMORE (AP) -- Joseph McLean scored 20 points and had six rebounds and Morgan State pulled away in the second half to defeat Norfolk State, 71-61, Monday night. Jamar Smith contributed 18 points and grabbed seven rebounds, Ronald Timus had 16 points and Jerrel Green had eight assists for Morgan (10-13, 8-4 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference), which shot 70 percent in the second half and 63.3 percent for the game. Corey Lyons had 19 points and Calvin Brown had 17 points and seven rebounds for Norfolk (8-15, 8-5), which was hurt by shooting just 7 of 22 (31.8 percent) from the free throw line. Trailing by 10 at halftime, Norfolk opened the second half with a 17-7 run and tied the game at 41 with 12:29 remaining after a basket from Rashid Cann. Morgan answered by outscoring Norfolk 30-20 to close out the game. Morgan opened the game with a 10-2 run before Norfolk eventually tied the score at 12 with 12:12 left in the first half, thanks in part to five points from Baltimore native Tynell Dunkley. Morgan then outscored Norfolk, 22-12, the rest of the first half to take a 34-24 halftime lead. Smith scored eight points during that span for the Bears, who shot 58.6 percent from the field during the opening 20 minutes.
